source.name: July 11th Waxahachie Thursday Night Doubles (2 matches in 3 hours)
source.details:
Update 7/8 9AM.
We have filled all available spots for this event. If you would like to be added to our waitlist, then email ntanner@wisd.org. Please include the name and UTR of you and your partner plus a phone number. 

-Event Date: Thursday, July 11th. 

-Matches will take place at 7PM and 8PM.

-Players - Join us for Verified UTR Matchplay. This event is open to all players and all levels. We will group players based on their UTR/level to provide competitive matches and level-based play.

-We will only accept first 16 doubles teams due to time and space.

- Get rated or improve your Verified UTR Rating. All scores count towards Verified UTR.

- All players will be placed in a 3-hour window, with a 2-match guarantee. 

- Matches will be 2 out of 3 FAST4 sets, no AD-scoring, 7pt tiebreak at 4-4, and 10pt super tiebreaker in lieu of 3rd set.

- Refund Policy: No refund on day of event.

***Disclaimer*** By entering the Waxahachie Tennis UTR you acknowledge Waxahachie Independent School District is not liable for injury to athletes or spectators.

source.name: COCKATOO JUNIOR HOLIDAY TOURNAMENT - Friday July 12th
source.details:
COCKATOO JUNIOR HOLIDAY UTR TENNIS TOURNAMENT

TOURNAMENT DATE:

Friday July 12th, 1:00pm-5:30pm

VENUE LOCATION:

Cockatoo Tennis Club,
2 McBride Street
Cockatoo, 3781

COURT SURFACE: Synthetic Grass 

This is a UTR verified Tournament.

TOURNAMENT FORMAT:

This Tournament is Open to all Junior Players 18 years old & Under with a UTR 1+ with 2 guaranteed matches

DRAW FORMAT:

- Back Match Draw
- 2 matches per player

SCORING FORMAT: 

Best of 2 Full Sets with 3rd Set 10 point Match Tiebreaker if required

DIVISION / LEVEL BREAKDOWN:

JUNIOR UTR BASED LEVEL SINGLES

This Division is open to all Juniors 18 & Under

EVENT FORMAT:

Players will be placed into Groups of 4 based on their UTR rating 

PRIZES:

- Winner of each Group will receive a Trophy

- Runner Up in each Group will receive a medal

- Winner of each Group Consolation Final will receive a medal

PRE-MATCH WARMUP: 

All players will receive a 5-minute warmup before each match.

DRAWS:

Draws will be posted the day before the Tournament & Details emailed to all players.

MATCH TIMES:

Matches will commence from 1:00pm

REFUND POLICY: 

- Cancelled events due to wet weather will receive a refund.
 
- Withdrawals after the registration deadline will not receive a refund.

Please contact Tim on 0404 352 049 for further Tournament details.

source.name: SETA Performance Camp & Match Play- Fri 12th JUL
source.details:
WEEK 1- Friday 12th

SETA Tennis Academy are running a Performance holiday camp & UTR verified Match play specifically for tournament players or those looking to start playing tournaments.

Come to our state of the art tennis club in Beaumaris and take your game to the next level.

Open to tournament level players with a UTR of between 0 and 10 (UTR 0-3.9, 4.0-6.9, 7.0-10.0). You do not need to be coached at SETA Tennis to participate. Option to enroll in individual or multiple days. 

If you're unsure if your child is appropriate for this camp contact Daniel on 0405 520 762 or admin@setacademy.com.au.

Schedule -

11:45am, Arrive. Check-in and stretch. 

12:00pm to 1:45pm - Warm-up & Athletic Development, on-court training

1:45pm to 2:30pm – Break with pre-match strategy and post-match analysis

2:30pm to 3.30pm - 1 UTR verified Singles Match

UTR Verified Singles Match Format - Best 2 of sets with first to 10 point match tiebreaker at 1 set all. - Singles match-ups will be based on UTR & maximising variety (i.e. where possible not playing regular training partners and not playing the same person across different camp days).

*please note that your match may be scheduled at Bodley Street Tennis Club (~400m from Beaumaris Lawn Tennis Club). By entering you give permission for you/your child to be walked over by a tennis coach to the Bodley Street Tennis Club if your match is scheduled there.
